to ask.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sam</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dotty,<P><b>There are some decent spells in the expansion: Tugur's,</b><P>Great spell, but forlorn deeds is almost as good. Very very close.<P><b>Regrowth</b><P>Druids get it too.<P><b>Superior Healing,</b><P>Clerics, druids, and paladins get it too.<P><b>Talisman of Kragg</b><P>Decent spell... the efficiency hasn't changed at ALL, though. It only adds 100 more HP.<P><b>BoN</b><P>Bane of Nife is a piece of sh*t. I've posted elsewhere the numbers explaining why.<P><b>Celerity</b><P>Woohoo.<P><b>Poxx</b><P>Now Pox of Bertox IS a good spell... the only really good spell we get, actually... and Pyrocruor is better.<P><b>Malo</b><P>Magicians essentially get it too.<P><b>The only real problem is the pet</b><P>The pet is a MAJOR problem, but it isn't the only one.<P>Sam<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Blart</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Make a post on the gameplay forums then.. i'll bump it.  Telling Shaman our lvl 50+ spells suck isn't new news.  I suggest you <b>stop</b> playing your shaman.  If enough people do, that will give Verant a sign that something is wrong with the new Shaman spells.<P><BR>In the meantime, make an iksar necro and twink the hell out of it.  It's hands down the most powerful race/class combo in the game.  The iksar natural regen + dark pact line of spells make for constant clarity.  Hell, my Iksar gains hitpoints with the level 20 allure of death spell on when sitting down.  If you can round up enough +INT items to get the iksar's intelligence up to 150 or so, you're set.<P>Blart 51 Mystic (retired)<P>Frybread Power - 20 Necro (3 days /played)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dotty</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just said they were good, I didn't say they were unique. Well, they are for evil shamans on my server (Tallon Zek) since we play racewar without crossteaming so there is no competition from druids and paladins, but anyway. A spell doesn't stop being good just because others get it. Of course, it does significantly affect the role of the shaman in a group, but I was just talking about the spells themselves.<P>I think Bane of Nife is fine, for the simply reason that it stacks with Ebolt. In just two castings you can have 2800 points of fast DoTs on the target - and the necros can take care of the Ebolt part. BoN should be more efficient though, I can agree.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mithranndir</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah I hate to say it becasue I really love(d) my shaman but the more I think about it I can't see much point in going on and on and on for little or no reward of ability or usefulness/effeciency above what I can do now with my shaman. The spells we get are lame and it's pointless to argue or defend the expansion spells becasue we all know it..the ones who fight it are just trying to convince themselves they havent wasted all this time. <P>So you're say, 56..annnnd...can't do what you were doing at 50+ any better than you could at 50...o-kay. So the impetus to continue is what?...it'd be a waste to start over? <P>Sorry, not good enough. <P>Damnit...I'm pissed. I want to have fun with my shaman again, look forward to getting tougher and better...and those days are gone.<P>crap.<P>------------------<BR>Mithranndir Stormcrow<BR>50th Season Barbarian Shaman<BR>Guild Dallow Abligo<BR>The Rathe Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dwilgar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Why do you keep saying that Forlorn Deeds is almost as good as Turgur's?<P>Turgur's is 6 levels sooner: 51 vs. 57<P>Turgur's is 8% more slowdown a