 Malosi to differentiate our abilities from the Magician's in this line of spells.  <P>And finally, this Avatar spell is pretty much ****e.  Give me a Str/Attack/Regen spell like Rage or Fury to stick on those tanks.  Make it last 1 minute, 200-300 mana, and cast time of 2 seconds (no recast time), similar to Burst of Strength.  <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skaar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dwilgar, sorry to say it, but I think you are reaching for something to like, something that is unique to shamans, in the post Kunark world.<P>75% vs 67% slowdown? Significant? You'd have to examine log files pretty close to even see a difference. 6+ mins vs 2 mins? OK, that's nice... for kiting I guess. I never kite so 6+ minutes is useless to me. It's a rare fight that lasts long enough for Plague to be worth casting, so 2 minutes seems ample on a melee slow down. Meleeing for over 2 minutes is a pretty bad idea at level 50+ anyway, even with attack slow downs.<BR>3 sec vs 6 sec casting time? Turgur's is only 25 more mana? None of this seems like a dramatic difference to me, especially considering that the lower level spell will oevr write the higher level one anyway. Take into account the fact that Enchanters can mez, charm, clarity, haste, debuff, etc.... Who will choose a shaman just for a 7% increase in attack slow downs? Nobody. And you know it, I suspect. Therfe are so many places now people say "you can't really do that area without an enchanter". WHo says that about shamans?<P>Dotty, you have chosen to say the "supplements" we got to our spell lines make up for the general lack of meaningful "enhancements". That's fine - for you. It's not fine for me. I have never been satisfied being invited into a group because they couldn't find a cleric. I want to have something valuable and unique I can add to a group. In the post-50 world, I don't. It's just that simple. Other classes have had to deal with this problem before. I just didn't expect it to happen to shamans. I don't understand why they crippled one of the only "balanced" classes in the game. I just don't.<P>And no, I will not start a new character. I don't like where verant has gone with Everquest. It's apparrent to me now that powerlevelling and collecting loot are all that there ever will be to do in this game. And that's just not very much fun anymore, especially when I am not looking forward to any of the new spells. <P>I have only logged into my server twice this week, and both times for less than 2 hours. That's WAY down from my normal playtime. I suspect it will not be long before I stop logging in at all. From what I can see, a lot of people have already stopped playing. I think Verant needs to examine server loads relative to a month ago instead of subscription rates if they want to see what the future holds for EQ. I suspect most people will keep their accounts active for some time after they stop playing. Just prior to Kunark shipping my server was averaging 2000 people during prime time. It's under 1500 now at the same times. My bet is a lot of those 1500 are playing twinks too, based on how empty the high level Kunark zones are. What happens when they decide they bored with their new characters too. <P>Verant, pull your head out. It may not be too late.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dwilgar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">8% greater slowdown is a huge effect when mobs are double hitting for 120+.<P>6 min duration is a great effect when you have multiple mobs to slow and it takes more than a minute to kill each one.<P>Fast casting time is great when a mob is beating your ass down and you have to slow it.<P>Getting the spell 6 levels soon is HUGE since I don't see many level 57 enchanters running around.  I see tons of level 51 and higher shaman.  Turgur's utterly destroys the second best enchanter slowdown spell (Shiftless Deeds).<P>Pound for pound Turgur's kicks ass -- end of story.<P>As regards picking a shaman over an enchanter, or vise versa, I was, and am, making no judgements on that situation.  The sole purpose of my comment was to point out that Turgur's is a much better spell than Forlorn Deeds, dispite continued statements of the opposite.<P>------------------<BR>Dwilgar<BR>High Shamaness of Oggok<BR>Rodcet Nife</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
